[node name="StoryText" type="RichTextLabel" parent="END" index="0"]
offset_left = 60.0
offset_top = -89.0
offset_right = 988.0
offset_bottom = 662.0
theme_type_variation = &"VoiceoverBox"
theme_override_font_sizes/normal_font_size = 30
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "You graduated your apprenticeship at nineteen, and have been working for four years since.

Your work takes you out into the forests and ruins as often as up to the Generators themselves. There was a time when the parts needed for their maintenance could be manufactured, but that time is long gone. Now, they must be salvaged from the cities and factories of old.

Hiking through ruins; prying open hatches to sift through rusted components in hopes of finding something useful; long journeys with only a few colleagues to talk to -- these things are routine to you.

But as anyone who's so much as [i]talked[/i] to as Salvager knows, routine can turn to calamity at any moment."

